    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1937-10-21T06:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1937-10-21T06:00:00-05:00" n="432"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d432">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">361.1121 <persName>Hrinkevich, Frank</persName>/2:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in the Soviet Union</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_DJE1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Davies</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Moscow</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1937-10-21T14:00:00+03:00"
                            >October 21, 1937—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 21—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>274. Embassy’s telegram 268, October 18, 11 a.m. Foreign Office stated orally
                    today at 1:00 p.m., that <persName corresp="#p_DE2">Durbrow</persName>, who is
                    en route from Berlin and will arrive this evening in Minsk, may not interview
                        <persName>Hrinkevich</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_DJE1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Davies</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
